1
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,200
Is this going to work?

2
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:28,960
He doesn't look rich.

3
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,760
Didn't you see his shoes?

4
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:32,479
Nikes.

5
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,370
Several hundred a pair.

6
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:35,960
And he's an athlete.

7
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:37,800
Staying at a hotel alone.

8
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,200
He must have money on him.

9
00:00:40,360 --> 00:00:41,560
You're pretty sharp.

10
00:00:41,760 --> 00:00:42,320
You bet.

11
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:48,400
According to the feedback from the school teachers,

12
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,060
when Wen Xian came to Jianglin for exams in 2007,

13
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:52,880
he stayed right here.

14
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:54,180
Let's check it out.

15
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:58,600
Hello.

16
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,400
We're from the Criminal Investigation Detachment.

17
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:01,600
We'd like to ask you some questions.

18
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:02,560
We hope you can cooperate.

19
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,720
Okay, certainly.

20
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,780
Do you recognize this person?

21
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,039
His name is Wen Xian.

22
00:01:10,039 --> 00:01:11,039
Think carefully.

23
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,400
In April 2007,

24
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,860
he stayed here for a while.

25
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:14,680
Fourteen or fifteen,

26
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,520
a student,

27
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:16,200
quite tall.

28
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:18,400
He likely carried a big long pole.

29
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:21,039
A pole?

30
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:23,440
Now that you mention it, I do recall something.

31
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:24,760
It's been over ten years.

32
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,400
This chair of mine,

33
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,600
he made it for me.

34
00:01:27,039 --> 00:01:27,680
So,

35
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,600
is there anything else?

36
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:29,520
Think again.

37
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:30,960
I remember

38
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,280
he came for an exam.

39
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,560
Always holding that pole.

40
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,400
He looked quite ragged.

41
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,039
Since a friend introduced him,

42
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:38,600
I didn't charge him much.

43
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:40,360
He was a kid from the countryside.

44
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,720
Just staying in the city for a few days for the exam.

45
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:44,200
That kid looked pitiful.

46
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,080
He had an exam but no sneakers.

47
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:48,320
He wore a pair of adult leather shoes.

48
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,600
They didn't fit him at all.

49
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,530
He was a good kid.

50
00:01:59,039 --> 00:01:59,759
Brother Han,

51
00:01:59,759 --> 00:02:01,640
I saw a pile of scrap in the backyard,

52
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,040
so I made you a chair.

53
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,400
That's great.

54
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:07,800
You're very skilled.

55
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,169
I learned a bit when I was young.

56
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:11,600
Wait a moment.

57
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,760
Take these shoes.

58
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,520
Take it as payment for making the chair.

59
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:21,240
Mr. Han.

60
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,160
I can't take this.

61
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,360
You've already given me a big discount on the rent.

62
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,360
Just take it.

63
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,320
You're taking an exam.

64
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,000
How can you not even have a pair of sneakers?

65
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,520
Can you get good results in those leather shoes?

66
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,250
Take it back.

67
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:32,640
Take it.

68
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,120
Thank you.

69
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,560
You're welcome.

70
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,620
Do well on the exam.

71
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,160
You can do it.

72
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:49,000
This chair is so exquisite.

73
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,720
It's lasted for so long.

74
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,760
The surface is all smooth and shiny.

75
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,720
Could a 14 or 15-year-old really have made this?

76
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,160
Yes.

77
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,440
It's very sturdy.

78
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:58,400
It hasn't broken in all these years.

79
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,320
It's a pity about that child.

80
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,640
He was tall and handsome.

81
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:02,040
If it weren't for what happened back then,

82
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,400
he would have had a bright future.

83
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,080
What happened?

84
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:04,800
Back then,

85
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:05,820
a man and a woman

86
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:06,920
waited until I was out

87
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,050
to pull a badger game in my guesthouse.

88
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:17,380
Where are you going this late?

89
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,120
Look how scared the kid is.

90
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:31,720
What a pity.

91
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,320
I didn't keep an eye on him,

92
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,920
so I missed out on making a buck.

93
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,640
It's a hassle carrying that pole.

94
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,520
It's not worth much anyway.

95
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,240
Since I'm here,

96
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,880
I can't go back empty-handed.

97
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,740
I can use it to dry clothes at home.

98
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:44,800
Let's go.

99
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,280
That kid ran off

100
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,800
without even taking his luggage.

101
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,860
He never came back.

102
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,780
What happened to his luggage?

103
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,640
We waited for months, but he never showed up.

104
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,440
So eventually,

105
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,840
we got rid of the luggage.

106
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:09,170
I wanted to call the police,

107
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,640
but I didn't have any evidence.

108
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,080
Besides,

109
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,120
I run a small business.

110
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,180
I couldn't risk it.

111
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,280
After that,

112
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,010
those two never came back here.

113
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,240
Thanks for your trouble.

114
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,519
According to the guesthouse owner,

115
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,000
Kang Zixin and Huang Hankun

116
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,130
conspired to trick Wen Xian back then.

117
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:27,720
They even took his vaulting pole,

118
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,360
causing him to miss the exam.

119
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,560
So Wen Xian holds a grudge against them.

120
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,440
He has a motive for murder.

121
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:35,120
It seems

122
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,240
he's been in hiding all these years

123
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,320
just to get revenge.

124
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,120
Now we just need to find Wen Xian

125
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,960
and run another DNA test

126
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:44,159
to see if he's the killer.

127
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:44,700
Listen.

128
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:45,640
Gao,

129
00:04:46,159 --> 00:04:46,620
Jin Jin,

130
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,920
you two go to the prison.

131
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,640
Find Wen Xian's birth mother

132
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,240
and see if you can find any clues.

133
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,320
Xu Jinghe

134
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,480
was sentenced when her son was five.

135
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,960
Since she arrived,

136
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,080
no one has visited her.

137
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,010
Not even her son.

138
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,920
We have a case where her son is a suspect.

139
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,360
We want to see if Xu Jinghe

140
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,720
can provide some details about him.

141
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:07,280
Okay.

142
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,720
I'll have someone bring her out.

143
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,580
You can ask her whatever you need.

144
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,440
We're from the Criminal Investigation Detachment of the Public Security Bureau.

145
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:12,840
We came here today...

146
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,500
I'm about to get out of prison.

147
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,920
Is there something unclear about the case?

148
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,880
Here's the thing.

149
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:20,080
You handed your son over to Wen Dong back then.

150
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,120
Wen Dong is dead.

151
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,810
Did you know about this?

152
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,120
My son Wen Xian...

153
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:24,960
How is he?

154
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:25,760
Rest assured.

155
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:26,690
Your son is fine.

156
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:27,760
The villagers

157
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,360
are also helping to take care of him.

158
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,820
Do you want to see your son?

159
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:32,680
Yes.

160
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,040
Of course I do.

161
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,320
I think about him every day.

162
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:37,580
There isn't a moment I don't think of him.

163
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,159
Take a look.

164
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,080
He's grown so much.

165
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:52,940
That's wonderful.

166
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,120
When you did it back then,

167
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:02,770
did your child know?

168
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,440
He didn't know.

169
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,690
He was sleeping in the room.

170
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:09,080
I checked the records.

171
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,240
You wanted to run.

172
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,060
Didn't you think about taking Wen Xian with you?

173
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,780
I thought about it.

174
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,320
But,

175
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,960
he'd only suffer with me.

176
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,490
If I left him in the village,

177
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,450
with all the neighbors around,

178
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,720
everyone would help raise him.

179
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,560
He was only five back then.

180
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,320
How could you bear it?

181
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,540
Didn't you think about

182
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:35,120
a child losing both parents overnight,

183
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,720
and how devastated he'd be?

184
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,450
His father was on drugs.

185
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,980
His mother was a murderer.

186
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,320
Such a cruel truth,

187
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:42,780
could you bear to tell him?

188
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:47,720
I couldn't.

189
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,120
So...

190
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,020
I begged the police back then,

191
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,280
and the neighbors,

192
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,080
not to tell Wen Xian

193
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,680
that I killed his father.

194
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,920
Just say we left.

195
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,840
It's been twenty years.

196
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:05,120
Didn't you think of keeping a memento?

197
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,200
Whenever I missed him,

198
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:11,040
I'd take out his hair and look at it.

199
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:12,640
Hair?

200
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,240
What hair?

201
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,320
Wen Xian's?

202
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,080
When I left back then,

203
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:22,160
I cut a lock of his hair to take with me.

204
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,580
Do you still have the hair?

205
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,680
I gave it to the guard.

206
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:58,180
What have you been thinking about on the way?

207
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,440
Nothing much.

208
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,640
It just feels like

209
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,440
I'm walking the same path my dad did.

210
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,320
Same here.

211
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:08,880
I also feel like

212
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,680
I'm walking the same path my master did.

213
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,920
So,

214
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,040
we need to prove that his hypothesis

215
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,740
is correct.

216
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,120
Let's go.

217
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,530
Here in the village,

218
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:31,000
this is all the information we have on them.

219
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,680
Thank you.

220
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:33,960
If you want to talk about

221
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,080
the Wen family,

222
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,600
it's a long story.

223
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:39,000
When Wen Xian was five years old,

224
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,799
his mother, Xu Jinghe, killed his father, Wen Nan.

225
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,410
What was the reason?

226
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,060
Wen Nan got hooked on drugs

227
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,160
and was abusive at home.

228
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,240
Xu Jinghe was sentenced to twenty years.

229
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:49,880
Their family

230
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,640
didn't have any other relatives.

231
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,600
So Wen Xian was entrusted to Wen Dong.

232
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,060
Some of the family's money

233
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,720
was given to him as well.

234
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,880
Who is Wen Dong?

235
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:58,980
What does he do?

236
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,480
Wen Dong

237
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,040
is Wen Xian's uncle.

238
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,080
He is also a skilled carpenter in our village.

239
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,000
So,

240
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,320
since he was little, Wen Xian

241
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,920
has been learning carpentry from his uncle.

242
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,250
He was just too naughty,

243
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,800
always jumping around.

244
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,400
He even got a pole,

245
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,260
and practiced pole vaulting here every day.

246
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:40,880
Thank you.

247
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,520
Thank you, everyone.

248
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,040
We're all neighbors.

249
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,340
No need to be so polite.

250
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,640
Wen Xian.

251
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,120
Did you hide the money well?

252
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,240
Be careful.

253
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,440
Don't let anyone steal it.

254
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,280
Don't worry.

255
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,160
I hid it well.

256
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,680
When you get to Jianglin,

257
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,920
find a hotel closest to the school.

258
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,320
Don't stay too far away,

259
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,780
or you might miss the exam.

260
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,360
I know.

261
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,930
Look at you, bringing a separate pole.

262
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,800
Just use this plastic one to carry your luggage.

263
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:04,400
Silly boy.

264
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,400
No.

265
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:07,120
This is my exam pole.

266
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,240
I only use it for exams and training.

267
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,450
It's very precious.

268
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,040
Wen Xian,

269
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,680
settle down once you get to the city.

270
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,720
Focus on the exam.

271
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,680
The villagers

272
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,640
are waiting for news of your success.

273
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,240
Good luck.

274
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,040
Okay. I'll do my best.

275
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,120
Did you know he went to the city for the exam?

276
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:24,560
Yes.

277
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:25,680
In our village,

278
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,440
there was a middle school PE teacher.

279
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,640
He felt that the kid

280
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,920
had a real talent for sports.

281
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,240
So he suggested

282
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,000
applying to a sports school.

283
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,600
Wen Xian really wanted to go.

284
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:36,440
But Wen Dong absolutely refused.

285
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,160
Why is that?

286
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:38,840
He just wanted Wen Xian

287
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,440
to learn a trade

288
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,240
and start earning money for him.

289
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:45,040
Why would he want to spend money on him?

290
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,600
Later, the villagers

291
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,160
felt sorry for the child.

292
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,400
Everyone pooled some travel expenses,

293
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,000
so Wen Xian

294
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,240
could go to the city for the exam.

295
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,760
Where is Wen Dong now?

296
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:56,780
He's long gone.

297
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:57,840
Where is his home?

298
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:58,640
Can you take us there?

299
00:10:58,640 --> 00:10:59,440
Okay.

300
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:00,570
Let's go.

301
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:01,400
Thank you.

302
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:03,720
Take a look.

303
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,440
This was Wen Dong's home.

304
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,440
A big fire burned it down to this.

305
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,040
What caused the fire?

306
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,540
When did it happen?

307
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,600
I heard Wen Dong got drunk that day,

308
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,120
and accidentally started the fire.

309
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,480
By the time they found him,

310
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,810
he was burned to a crisp.

311
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:19,880
That day,

312
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,280
happened to be the day Wen Xian was taking an exam in the city.

313
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,680
So I remember it clearly.

314
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,120
Did he come back then?

315
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,640
No.

316
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,120
They didn't tell him at the time.

317
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,200
Because they were afraid

318
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,240
it would distract him from his exam.

319
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:29,920
Later,

320
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,280
he came back for his uncle's burial.

321
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,840
Is this key from here?

322
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:01,400
It is from here.

323
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:05,000
There was Wen Xian's hair at Xu Jinghe's place.

324
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,600
Gao Zhuang has retrieved it.

325
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,880
We've already run the comparison.

326
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,680
The results will be out tonight.

327
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:11,720
Right.

328
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,440
You have a package.

329
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,700
I'm holding it for you.

330
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:16,800
Okay.

331
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:17,930
I'll open it for you.

332
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,130
Whose package is it?

333
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,440
Captain Zheng's.

334
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:28,920
What is this?

335
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:31,600
A raincoat.

336
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,080
Don't we have plenty of these at the station?

337
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,000
It's bulging.

338
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,240
Gloves.

339
00:12:59,240 --> 00:12:59,880
Morning.

340
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,080
Morning.

341
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:01,940
Captain Zheng.

342
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,540
The semen DNA from the Kang Zixin case

343
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:08,770
belongs to Wen Xian.

344
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,240
By the way, Chen Yishi,

345
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,120
where is my package?

346
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,000
What's inside?

347
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,080
Captain Zheng.

348
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,680
Your package was a raincoat.

349
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,840
There was a pair of gloves in the pocket.

350
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:29,920
One of them had blood on it.

351
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,650
I ran a bio-analysis overnight

352
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,080
and found two sets of DNA.

353
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:33,720
Of those,

354
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,650
the blood belongs to Huang Hankun.

355
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,200
The skin flakes inside the glove

356
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,600
matched the hair provided by Xu Jinghe

357
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,800
perfectly.

358
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,140
It belongs to Wen Xian.

359
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,130
And regarding that coat...

360
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:45,640
What is it? Tell me.

361
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:46,680
I'll explain.

362
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,520
From that raincoat,

363
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:49,800
we extracted another set of DNA from the collar.

364
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,000
We can only confirm it's a male,

365
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,200
but we can't identify him.

366
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,600
But that raincoat is the one the dumper wore.

367
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,480
It appeared on surveillance three times in total.

368
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,680
Once by the Bahe River,

369
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,120
and twice at the 101 Bar.

370
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,160
Tell me,

371
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,960
did you just meet Xu Haishan?

372
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,200
Yes.

373
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,320
So, I think it went like this.

374
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,120
Chief Fu.

375
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,520
Group Leader Yan.

376
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:16,880
Just in time.

377
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,010
I need to talk to you.

378
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,760
Do you want to know

379
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:21,930
why I wouldn't let you see Haishan?

380
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,440
And do you want to know

381
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,360
why Xu Haishan

382
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:26,760
is still alive?

383
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,680
Do you also want to know

384
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,940
what Haishan has been through in the last eleven years?

385
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,420
To be honest, Chief Fu,

386
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,160
I really want to know.

387
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:43,280
But I'm well aware of our protocols.

388
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,210
Don't ask what shouldn't be asked.

389
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,420
Just knowing Haishan is alive

390
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,280
is a great relief.

391
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,920
You've made great progress.

392
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,320
You're becoming more mature and steady.

393
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,000
As a qualified detective,

394
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,760
you should be just like this,

395
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,440
always keeping a cool head.

396
00:15:01,520 --> 00:15:02,440
You know,

397
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,200
looking at it now,

398
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,680
I didn't let you join our task force back then,

399
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,340
and I actually regret it a bit.

400
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,360
Tell me.

401
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,690
What do you want with me?

402
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:13,240
We received a raincoat

403
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,480
with a pair of bloody gloves inside.

404
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,520
On them,

405
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,250
we found DNA from three people.

406
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:20,080
Suspect Wen Xian.

407
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,680
Victim Huang Hankun.

408
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:23,080
And

409
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,000
Xu Haishan.

410
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:28,200
Go on.

411
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:30,120
We're puzzled.

412
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,170
Why would Xu Haishan

413
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:34,840
be connected to the suspect and the victim?

414
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,680
So,

415
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,720
we wanted to speak with you

416
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,850
and Group Leader Yan

417
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,120
to discuss this.

418
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,120
Let me see the files on Huang Hankun

419
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,680
and Wen Xian first.

420
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:54,280
Old Yan.

421
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,340
Take a look at this.

422
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,760
Then let's start

423
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:07,840
from when

424
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:10,200
Haishan joined the force.

425
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,780
Because of that incident,

426
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:12,440
I

427
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,400
and Group Leader Yan...

428
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,530
And Dai Yu's father,

429
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,360
because of Haishan's background,

430
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:17,600
even had a disagreement.

431
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,530
I don't agree with recruiting him.

432
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,560
Rules are rules.

433
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,840
His mother is a criminal.

434
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,440
That is a security risk.

435
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,800
It's such a pity.

436
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,040
Xu Haishan...

437
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,800
grew up in an orphanage.

438
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,440
He's such a good kid.

439
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:36,640
I really,

440
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,170
from the bottom of my heart,

441
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,400
feel sorry for him.

442
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:40,360
That kid,

443
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,280
is top-notch in every way.

444
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,130
He's solid in every aspect.

445
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,770
Especially that spirit of his.

446
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:49,130
Where else can you find someone like that?

447
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:52,320
What's wrong?

448
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:53,580
Why the long faces?

449
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,040
I have good news for you.

450
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:59,440
Xu Jinghe isn't Xu Haishan's biological mother at all.

451
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,200
What happened?

452
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,000
Tell us.

453
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,400
I just came back from the prison.

454
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,400
Xu Jinghe told me,

455
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,329
that kid isn't her biological son.

456
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,319
Xu Haishan...

457
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,160
I found him.

458
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,359
When I was getting married,

459
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,440
I saw something abandoned by the road,

460
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,369
a blood-stained swaddling cloth.

461
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,440
I thought it was a dead baby.

462
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,859
Everyone said it was bad luck.

463
00:17:21,960 --> 00:17:24,240
But I saw that the child was still alive.

464
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,240
I couldn't bear

465
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,359
to leave him by the roadside all alone.

466
00:17:27,359 --> 00:17:28,079
So,

467
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,240
I took him to my ex-husband's house.

468
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,000
My ex-husband, Xu Zhijun,

469
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,800
was a good man.

470
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:35,800
He said

471
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,800
that this was a gift from heaven.

472
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,040
So,

473
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,240
we raised him

474
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,920
as our own son.

475
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,840
I never told Haishan

476
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,000
that I found him.

477
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,000
My ex-husband died.

478
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:50,920
Later,

479
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:53,320
I remarried Wen Nan.

480
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:56,520
But Wen Nan refused to keep Haishan,

481
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:59,050
especially after I gave birth to Wen Xian.

482
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:01,000
I had no choice

483
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,760
but to send him to an orphanage.

484
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,320
After Wen Xian was born,

485
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,320
Xu Jinghe

486
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,600
sent Xu Haishan to the orphanage.

487
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,260
So after that, Haishan

488
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,840
lived in an orphanage.

489
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,840
But Xu Jinghe visited Xu Haishan often.

490
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:16,280
So Xu Haishan

491
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:17,880
still cared about Xu Jinghe.

492
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:29,960
Haishan.

493
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,240
It's not that I don't want you.

494
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,440
There are too many people at home,

495
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,570
and there's no room.

496
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,490
I'm sending you somewhere to stay for a while.

497
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,640
I'll visit you often.

498
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,440
When I have time, I'll bring you home.

499
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:42,960
Okay?

500
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:43,760
Mom.

501
00:18:43,760 --> 00:18:45,000
I don't want to leave you.

502
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,720
I want to stay with you.

503
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,400
Please don't send me away.

504
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,040
Later, Xu Jinghe went to prison.

505
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,080
Wen Xian

506
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,840
was given to his uncle to raise.

507
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,080
But Haishan

508
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,560
was deeply loyal

509
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,640
and never forgot his younger brother.

510
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,560
Can this child's

511
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:09,840
biological parents be found?

512
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:12,320
Based on when and where Xu Jinghe found him,

513
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:14,560
I sent people to investigate the nearby villages.

514
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:16,080
A boy less than six months old

515
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,240
was found by Xu Jinghe.

516
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:17,920
That person

517
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,040
is Xu Haishan.

518
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:22,160
I also checked his biological data extensively.

519
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:24,120
There are no issues with his background.

520
00:19:24,120 --> 00:19:24,720
Later,

521
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,920
when we needed to choose

522
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,000
an undercover agent,

523
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
your father and I

524
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,580
selected Haishan.

525
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:31,370
For all these years,

526
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:33,240
Haishan has been hiding,

527
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,320
standing in the dark corners.

528
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:37,850
He held firm to his convictions

529
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:39,740
and his faith as a police officer.

530
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,440
We all have the utmost respect for him.
